posts.title: GitHub
posts.content: GitHub is a developer platform that allows developers to create, store, manage and share their code. It uses Git software, providing the distributed version control of Git plus access control, bug tracking, software feature requests, task management, continuous integration, and wikis for every project.

posts.title: My JSON Server
posts.content:
How to
Create a repository on GitHub (<your-username>/<your-repo>)
Create a db.json file
Visit https://my-json-server.typicode.com/<your-username>/<your-repo> to access your server

posts.title: Example
posts.content:
You can check the following server as an example:
https://my-json-server.typicode.com/typicode/demo
